title: BRIEF-Genentech Phase III IMblaze370 Study Did Not Meet Primary Endpoint Compared To Regorafenib
text:
May 10 (Reuters) -
* GENENTECH PROVIDES UPDATE ON PHASE III STUDY OF TECENTRIQ (ATEZOLIZUMAB) AND COTELLIC (COBIMETINIB) IN PEOPLE WITH HEAVILY PRE-TREATED LOCALLY ADVANCED OR METASTATIC COLORECTAL CANCER
* GENENTECH - PHASE III IMBLAZE370 STUDY EVALUATING COMBINATION OF TECENTRIQ AND COTELLIC DID NOT MEET PRIMARY ENDPOINT OF OVERALL SURVIVAL COMPARED TO REGORAFENIB
* GENENTECH- RESULTS FROM IMBLAZE370 SHOWED TREATMENT WITH TECENTRIQ ALONE DID NOT PROVIDE MEANINGFUL CLINICAL BENEFIT COMPARED TO REGORAFENIB Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:
